search::createSearchArray()

Description
    private array search::createSearchArray(void)
    Creates an array from submitted form data.

Return Values
    An array containing data submitted via a search form.
    
Examples
    <?php
	...
	if (empty($this->engine->cleanPost['HTML']['searchString'][0])) {
	   if ($this->disableEmptySearch) {
		return webHelper_errorMsg("No search keywords entered.");
	   }
	   else {
		$this->relevanceSearch = FALSE;
	   }
	}
		
	$output  = NULL;
	$results = array();
	$this->searchArray = $this->createSearchArray();
	...
    ?>
    
See Also
    search::submit()
    search::searchStringToArray()
